Rating: 4
Adore this cake, and have made it so many times that I've changed it and made it in some ways simpler. Following someone else's advice, I use 1 tsp. cinnamon, 1 tsp. salt, and 1/2 tsp. each of cloves, nutmeg, and allspice. Instead of boiling carrots, I just buy a can of carrots and mash them. I drain 1/2 cup of my pineapple juice into a measuring cup and then do only 1/2 cup of oil. Oh, and I just use the whole darn can of crushed pineapple...what do you do otherwise with that teensy bit of pineapple that's left over? I also do 1 c. of white sugar and 1/2 cup of brown sugar. Lastly, I put the 1 cup of coconut and 1 cup of walnuts into a frying pan and carefully carefully carefully brown them before adding to the recipe--adds lots more depth to the flavor! I always have leftover coconut and walnuts, so when the cake goes in the oven, I carefully brown them, let them cool, and then smoosh around the outside of the cake after it's frosted (2 layer cake, that is!) Of course, gotta double the frosting recipe!

