I made this cake last week for a friend's birthday and it was a huge hit. One friend at the party said he hates cake but really liked this one- he said it tasted like a muffen. I followed the cake recipe exactly but made a double layer cake using two 8 inch pans (cooked for about 35 minutes). I realized early on there wasn't going to be nearly enough frosting for a double layer cake. I used a total of 16 oz of cream cheese (egad!), 1.5 cups of powdered sugar, 6T butter, 1T lemon juice and 1t vanilla. To keep the frosting crumb-free I recommend spreading a thin layer of frosting over the cake to catch all the loose crumbs, putting the cake in the fridge for 10 minutes to set, then putting on the final frosting layer.

